data.name: txtChangelog.Text
data.value:
Changes in V2.1 (4/9/2018) - Fixed AutoGenerate to display all values correctly. - Removed some information from AutoGen - Improved perfomance of AutoGen by removing redundancies in the code. (log(log(n))) times faster, where n is the number of iterations. - Fixed the status bar from bugging out. - Other various fixes. - Sidenote: I release the application and I still find bugs... VERY FUN!
Changes in V2.03 + 2.04 (4/4/2018) - Added new setting to keep RSG topmost window. - Added Insanity for the random theme, its what it says. - Version now appears in the changelog header. - Fixed fatal runtime error caused by signing application.
Changes in V2.02 (4/3/2018) - Minor bug fixes
Changes in V2.01 (4/2/2018) - Tried to fix a report bug error, not necessarily fixed as of yet.
Changes in V2.0 (3/30/2018) This is an immense update from the previous version. The whole program is different at least internally. For some reason, I opened up this project just to look at the code and all of the sudden, I started fixing bugs, finalizing previous features and adding a ton of new, amazing things. After months of doing that, here's 2.0. This program runs on my new API (engine) which uses code from my personal codebank. The code is more modular in this edition.
NEW Search: + Search a specific string and in realtime, see how long it will take. + Display's various statistics regarding the runtime and time elapsed etc. + Can be executed many times on multiple threads. + Fixed internal CPU leak when searching two strings separately. + Added two different methods of expecting the character list. + Added more information regarding the string. + Added display heavy statistics to show much more information, with using a little bit more resources.
NEW Dictionary: + Added a dictionary form to generate random words + Ability to create your own dictionary to generate words from + Ability to have certain rules for your generation like capitalizing each word and use spaces, punctuation, noise, alliterations, etc. - The dictionary supports all unicode characters. - The program upon first load will ask for a directory to download and store your new dictionaries. - Display's various statistics regarding the iterated dictionary ruleset.
Main form update: + Added a characters button on the toolstrip. + Added check for updates button on toolstrip. + Added a status bar to show process information and memory usage. + Added a generate log file for the instance. + Added ability to report a bug! + Added a help window feature to show illustrative pictures demonstrating various program features. - Revamped the main form, added more shortcuts. - Rewrote the statistics function to work hundreds of times faster. - Updating the string length, and iterations updates on all other active forms which use it.
Settings update: + Added new theme(s) Warm, and Random! + Added tooltips for various properties for more information. - The theme colors are different and support all forms. - Rewrote the properties code to save upon exit and load saved settings. - Revamped about tab (added my link to portfolio).
Auto Generate update: - Rewrote the entire form internally and externally! - A little bit smarter, it recognizes the character list and string length from the main form to save you a bit of time. - Threaded task by default to make sure you can use other features of the program. + Added right click menu for the statistics list. - Able to export the text in the statistics list. - Able to find a specific string instance if there is in the list. + Start, stop, and refresh are all working fluently.
General changes: + Everything, at least internally.
Changes in V 1.0.1.0 (7/13/2017) - Cleaning up the program a bit more. - Added more stuff.
Changes in V 1.0.0.9 (1/14/2017) - Cleaning up the program.
Changes in V 1.0.0.8 (11/16/2016) Adding a few things to help make things easier. - Added option to save generated text to clipboard. - If there is more than one iteration, it saves the last iteration to clipboard. - Enabled by default, its toggleable in the Settings/Properties tab. - Added an auto generate function. - File/Auto Generate - Start and stop X number iterations or loop infinity.
Changes in V 1.0.0.7 (9/16/2016) - Reap-random randomization method is now properly implemented. - Randomizes a seed for each iteration to randomize (Much more random). - Added key shortcuts for certain actions. - Added more themes - Added a new function to Iterate a certain string configuration. - Reports the average statistics for the configuration. - Added 23 languages!
Changes in V 1.0.0.6 (6/5/2016) - Added support to change the randomness of the generate random text. - Added the Reap-random randomization method. - Added a few icons (Uppercase letter icon, Reap-random icon). - Added more functionality to add/remove characters in the string options tab in settings. - Rewritten a few functions to accept more parameters. - Fixed some bug(s).
Changes in V 1.0.0.5 - Added a changelog tab (what you're viewing here) - Added support for adding and removing characters. (enables the program to generate characters in other languages)
Changes in V 1.0.0.4 - Released to the public as the new, official beta. Changes in V 1.0.0.3 - Added the entire settings form. - String options tab - Performance tab - Properties tab - About tab
- Program can now check for updates - The program supports the use of arbitrarily large numbers. - Supports exact permuations of strings.
Changes in V 1.0.0.2 - Added support for changing the number of iterations
Changes in V 1.0.0.1 - Created a new project. - Plan to rewrite the entire program to increase readability over the years.
Changes in V 1.0.0.0 The original program viewed on YouTube.

data.name: lblAbout.Text
data.value: The random string generator is a piece of software developed by iReapism. Generates random strings of any unicode characters, able to test strings, and iterate string configurations of your choice. Also some other nifty features which makes it unique.
